  "Broker Comment" : "REQ'D AMENDED PAGE 3 FROM DELAWARE DISTRIBUTORS, INC., DISCLOSES THAT ON 5/27/79, NORTON DID COMMIT THE OFFENSE OF PETIT LARCENY A MISDEMEANOR IN VIOLATION OF SECTION 155.25 OF THE PENAL LAW OF THE STATE OF NEW YORK IN THAT HE DID STEAL PORPERTY OF ANOTHER HAVING VALUE OF LESS THAN $250. WHILE AT THE ROUTE 50 PRICE CHOPPER, IN SARATOGA SPRINGS, NEW YORK, NORTON PLACED TWO PACKAGES OF SIRLOIN TIP STEAK, TOTAL VALUE $4.88 IN HIS WAIST BAND BEHIND HIS BACK, AND COVERED SAME WITH HIS COAT. SUBSEQUENTLY, ON 6/11/79, NORTON PLEADED GUILTY TO VIOLATION OF SECTION 240.20 OF THE PENAL LAW (DISORDERLY CONDUCT). HE PAID A $50.00 FINE. (COURT DOCUMENTS FROM CRIMINAL CITY COURT, CITY OF SARATOGA SPRINGS, STATE OF NEW YORK WERE ATTACHED)."
